snippet.textDisplay: AMD said they would support AM4 until 2020, not segment AM4 motherboard compatibility. They have no justification for fucking over their users like this when they were so late with the B550 launch and many people reasonably bought a B450 or X470 instead expecting an upgrade path based on previous statements by AMD. The issue is the BIOS chip, but the thing is, many B450 and ALL X470 boards have the required 32MB BIOS chip. The restriction on those boards is entirely artificial and smells of Kaby Lake 2.0 ...come on AMD. The upgrade path was a large reason why your platform gained popularity even when it wasn't on par with Intel yet. I could understand if the new chipset brought something monumental to the table like DDR5, but it doesn't. PCIe 4 isn't that big of a deal as you can simply disable it on unsupported boards like with Ryzen 3000. The increased core performance is more important anyway. They need to do what they did with the 300 series boards and allow motherboard vendors to patch in support on a case by case basis for boards with the big BIOS chip.
